This paper is about network multiple-input and multiple-output (netMIMO) in wireless local area networks (WLAN), which involves the use of multiple antennas to improve wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses interference alignment and cancelation, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper covers distributed synchronization, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses interference and contention mitigation, which is related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
